cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL

This paper discusses plagiarism detection using natural language processing techniques such as n-gram co-occurrence statistics, skip-bigram, and longest common subsequence, which are commonly used in computational linguistics and information retrieval (cs.CL, cs.IR). The paper also proposes the use of WordNet, a lexical database that provides semantic information, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG).
